HEADWORD: Olivil
<hw>Ol`i*vil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>olivile</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
substance, obtained from an exudation from the olive, and having a
bitter-sweet taste and acid properties.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>olivile</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Gregory.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

